1
00:02:13,572 --> 00:02:16,572
There are other people involved!

2
00:03:17,570 --> 00:03:20,470
Teenaged Journey, narrating:
<i>Mama named me Journey.</i>

3
00:03:20,570 --> 00:03:21,471
<i>Journey...</i>

4
00:03:21,571 --> 00:03:25,470
<i>As if somehow she wished
her restlessness on me.</i>

5
00:03:25,570 --> 00:03:28,470
<i>But it was mama who
would be gone when I was 11,</i>

6
00:03:28,570 --> 00:03:31,470
<i>before spring
crashed onto our hillside</i>

7
00:03:31,570 --> 00:03:33,469
<i>with explosions
from mount Laurel,</i>

8
00:03:33,569 --> 00:03:35,469
<i>before summer came,</i>

9
00:03:35,569 --> 00:03:37,469
<i>with the soft slap
of the screen door,</i>

10
00:03:37,569 --> 00:03:39,469
<i>breathless nights and mildew</i>

11
00:03:39,569 --> 00:03:41,569
<i>on the books.</i>

12
00:03:43,569 --> 00:03:45,469
You shouldn't do this.
It's wrong.

13
00:03:45,569 --> 00:03:48,469
I can't live here anymore.

14
00:03:48,569 --> 00:03:51,469
You're always telling me
what I do wrong.

15
00:03:51,569 --> 00:03:53,469
It's your house, too.
Your children.

16
00:03:53,569 --> 00:03:55,469
They have you.

17
00:03:55,569 --> 00:03:58,469
I'm not enough, Min.

18
00:03:58,569 --> 00:03:59,470
Oh, yes, you are.

19
00:03:59,570 --> 00:04:01,469
You fill up this house, Marcus.

20
00:04:01,569 --> 00:04:03,468
It's your house, your land,

21
00:04:03,568 --> 00:04:05,468
your grandchildren, your rules.

22
00:04:05,568 --> 00:04:07,468
And my fault,
like it's always been.

23
00:04:07,568 --> 00:04:09,468
Someone else's fault.

24
00:04:09,568 --> 00:04:11,468
I can't be
what you want, Marcus.

25
00:04:11,568 --> 00:04:13,468
I never could.

26
00:04:13,568 --> 00:04:14,469
Even when I was little,

27
00:04:14,569 --> 00:04:17,468
you remember when I wanted
to ride the tractor with you?

28
00:04:17,568 --> 00:04:19,468
You said I shouldn't.

29
00:04:19,568 --> 00:04:21,468
When I wanted to work in town,

30
00:04:21,568 --> 00:04:23,468
you said I shouldn't.

31
00:04:23,568 --> 00:04:25,468
When I wanted
to go away to school,

32
00:04:25,568 --> 00:04:27,468
you made me stay here.

33
00:04:27,568 --> 00:04:29,468
Oh, that was a long time ago.

34
00:04:29,568 --> 00:04:32,567
Yeah. You gave up on me
a long time ago.

35
00:04:38,567 --> 00:04:40,467
Is it my fault he left you, too?

36
00:04:40,567 --> 00:04:41,717
I don't think so.

37
00:04:46,318 --> 00:04:47,468
Nobody leaves this place.

38
00:04:47,568 --> 00:04:49,467
Family's lived here forever.

39
00:04:49,567 --> 00:04:52,567
Our family doesn't go away.

40
00:05:01,566 --> 00:05:04,466
I go away.

41
00:05:04,566 --> 00:05:07,466
It isn't fair
to Journey and Cat.

42
00:05:07,566 --> 00:05:09,466
You come and go like a visitor.

43
00:05:09,566 --> 00:05:12,466
That's not a mother's way.

44
00:05:12,566 --> 00:05:14,566
Don't come back.

45
00:06:25,564 --> 00:06:28,464
When I was little,

46
00:06:28,564 --> 00:06:30,464
I used to stare
at daddy's picture,

47
00:06:30,564 --> 00:06:33,463
try to remember him.

48
00:06:33,563 --> 00:06:35,463
Tried to place the picture

49
00:06:35,563 --> 00:06:37,563
so his eyes
would look into mine.

50
00:06:39,563 --> 00:06:42,463
They never did.

51
00:06:42,563 --> 00:06:44,563
They always looked past me.

52
00:06:53,563 --> 00:06:56,463
Do you remember him?

53
00:06:56,563 --> 00:06:58,563
Do you know why daddy ran away?

54
00:07:02,313 --> 00:07:03,463
No one talks about it.

55
00:07:03,563 --> 00:07:06,562
I don't even think about him.

56
00:07:33,312 --> 00:07:34,462
She's leaving.

57
00:07:34,562 --> 00:07:37,561
Again?

58
00:08:07,560 --> 00:08:09,460
She's got a suitcase.

59
00:08:09,560 --> 00:08:11,560
No. No!

60
00:08:37,559 --> 00:08:39,559
I'll send money
for Cat and Journey.

61
00:08:41,559 --> 00:08:43,459
They're better off here.

62
00:08:43,559 --> 00:08:47,459
It's not good enough, Min.

63
00:08:47,559 --> 00:08:49,559
I'll call.

64
00:08:50,559 --> 00:08:52,559
Mom.

65
00:09:01,558 --> 00:09:03,458
I'll come back, Journey.

66
00:09:03,558 --> 00:09:07,558
No, son, she won't be back.

67
00:09:26,558 --> 00:09:28,558
Mama?

68
00:10:18,556 --> 00:10:21,456
She won't be back.

69
00:10:21,556 --> 00:10:22,706
Oof!

70
00:10:31,555 --> 00:10:33,555
Oh!

71
00:10:35,555 --> 00:10:37,555
Oh, no.

72
00:10:58,555 --> 00:11:00,454
Lottie?

73
00:11:00,554 --> 00:11:01,704
Lott...

74
00:11:06,554 --> 00:11:09,554
Ohh...

75
00:11:11,554 --> 00:11:16,454
That's all we have
of Min and the children.

76
00:11:16,554 --> 00:11:18,554
Oh, Lottie.

77
00:11:21,554 --> 00:11:23,454
Cat?

78
00:11:23,554 --> 00:11:25,554
Cat?

79
00:11:57,304 --> 00:11:58,454
Where you going?

80
00:11:58,554 --> 00:12:00,452
I'm rearranging my life.

81
00:12:00,552 --> 00:12:02,452
I don't want my camera,
mama's recorder,

82
00:12:02,552 --> 00:12:05,452
and most everything
else. Including meat.

83
00:12:05,552 --> 00:12:07,452
I spent yesterday
looking into a cow's eyes,

84
00:12:07,552 --> 00:12:10,452
and I will be a vegetarian.

85
00:12:10,552 --> 00:12:12,552
Which cow?

86
00:12:23,552 --> 00:12:24,702
Tired of this, Cat?

87
00:12:28,552 --> 00:12:31,451
My pictures are so...

88
00:12:31,551 --> 00:12:33,551
Boring?

89
00:12:35,551 --> 00:12:37,451
You're right, grandpa.

90
00:12:37,551 --> 00:12:39,551
You take it.

91
00:12:43,302 --> 00:12:44,452
Journey?

92
00:12:44,552 --> 00:12:46,451
I know the farm.

93
00:12:46,551 --> 00:12:48,451
Why would I need to
take pictures of it?

94
00:12:48,551 --> 00:12:50,551
Oh.

95
00:13:07,550 --> 00:13:09,450
Oh, look.
A recorder.

96
00:13:09,550 --> 00:13:11,450
I used to play the recorder.

97
00:13:11,550 --> 00:13:13,550
A long time ago, remember?

98
00:13:19,550 --> 00:13:21,550
Oh, look.

99
00:13:24,550 --> 00:13:26,550
That's mama's shirt.

100
00:13:28,550 --> 00:13:31,449
Journey...

101
00:13:31,549 --> 00:13:32,450
Come here.

102
00:13:32,550 --> 00:13:34,449
Come here, come here.

103
00:13:34,549 --> 00:13:35,449
Cat, come here.

104
00:13:35,549 --> 00:13:36,699
It's o.K.

105
00:13:39,549 --> 00:13:43,449
Lottie?

106
00:13:43,549 --> 00:13:45,549
Turn around.

107
00:14:42,547 --> 00:14:45,447
Good morning, Journey.

108
00:14:45,547 --> 00:14:48,447
Looking for your grandfather?

109
00:14:48,547 --> 00:14:49,697
No.

110
00:14:54,547 --> 00:14:56,547
Where is he?

111
00:14:58,546 --> 00:15:01,546
Taking pictures of cow pies.

112
00:15:17,546 --> 00:15:19,546
Sorry about your mama, Journey.

113
00:15:22,546 --> 00:15:24,546
She'll be back.

114
00:16:36,543 --> 00:16:38,443
Oh, Marcus!

115
00:16:38,543 --> 00:16:39,761
I'm getting
really tired of that.

116
00:16:57,292 --> 00:16:58,442
Hi, Cat.

117
00:16:58,542 --> 00:16:59,692
Thank you.

118
00:17:20,542 --> 00:17:22,542
No return address.

119
00:17:24,293 --> 00:17:25,443
I expect she won't...

120
00:17:25,543 --> 00:17:28,441
Marcus...

121
00:17:28,541 --> 00:17:29,691
Let it be.

122
00:17:32,541 --> 00:17:34,441
I think...

123
00:17:34,541 --> 00:17:35,442
That what grandpa means...

124
00:17:35,542 --> 00:17:38,441
Is that there'll be
money in the envelope,

125
00:17:38,541 --> 00:17:39,442
not words,

126
00:17:39,542 --> 00:17:41,441
not the words you want.

127
00:17:41,541 --> 00:17:44,541
You'll be disappointed.

128
00:17:50,541 --> 00:17:52,441
I'm not disappointed!
I'm not!

129
00:17:52,541 --> 00:17:54,441
There are words.

130
00:17:54,541 --> 00:17:56,441
Our names are there.
Our names are words.

131
00:17:56,541 --> 00:17:58,440
Journey, you keep the money.

132
00:17:58,540 --> 00:18:00,440
Do what you want with it.

133
00:18:00,540 --> 00:18:03,540
I'll put it in the bank.

134
00:18:05,291 --> 00:18:06,441
I'll start a child account.

135
00:18:06,541 --> 00:18:09,440
When mama tells where she is,
we could visit.

136
00:18:09,540 --> 00:18:10,441
She forgot the return address.

137
00:18:10,541 --> 00:18:13,540
She forgot. That's all.

138
00:18:32,539 --> 00:18:34,539
Oh, Journey.

139
00:18:48,539 --> 00:18:50,439
Why do you do that?

140
00:18:50,539 --> 00:18:52,539
Why?

141
00:18:55,539 --> 00:18:57,438
'Cause he needs to.

142
00:18:57,538 --> 00:18:59,438
I don't understand.

143
00:18:59,538 --> 00:19:01,538
I know, honey, I know.

144
00:20:30,535 --> 00:20:31,685
Journey?

145
00:20:33,535 --> 00:20:35,535
Come here.

146
00:20:40,535 --> 00:20:42,535
Let's look at these.

147
00:20:45,535 --> 00:20:47,535
There's your great-uncle Tom.

148
00:20:50,535 --> 00:20:53,435
Oh, and your cousin Bob.

149
00:20:53,535 --> 00:20:54,685
Remember him?

150
00:21:00,285 --> 00:21:01,435
Ahh.

151
00:21:01,535 --> 00:21:04,434
And that's me...

152
00:21:04,534 --> 00:21:07,534
When I was Cat's age.

153
00:21:11,534 --> 00:21:14,434
And that's me again.

154
00:21:14,534 --> 00:21:18,534
Now, that was taken
on a long-ago 4th of July.

155
00:21:19,534 --> 00:21:21,434
You look happy.

156
00:21:21,534 --> 00:21:22,435
I was happy.

157
00:21:22,535 --> 00:21:24,534
That was the day
I met your grandpa.

158
00:21:28,533 --> 00:21:30,433
Aw, and there's your mother...

159
00:21:30,533 --> 00:21:35,433
Same age, same date,
many years later.

160
00:21:35,533 --> 00:21:37,433
Hey, that's aunt Lacy
and uncle Maynard.

161
00:21:37,533 --> 00:21:38,434
That's right.

162
00:21:38,534 --> 00:21:41,433
Your grandpa took that picture.

163
00:21:41,533 --> 00:21:43,533
It's a good picture.

164
00:21:45,533 --> 00:21:47,533
Except for mama.

165
00:21:49,533 --> 00:21:51,533
Journey.

166
00:21:53,533 --> 00:21:56,432
Now, your mama always
wanted to be somewhere else.

167
00:21:56,532 --> 00:22:00,432
Well, now she is...

168
00:22:00,532 --> 00:22:02,532
Somewhere else.

169
00:23:24,279 --> 00:23:25,429
Wait!

170
00:23:25,529 --> 00:23:26,430
Mama!

171
00:23:26,530 --> 00:23:28,529
Wait, mama!

172
00:23:30,529 --> 00:23:32,529
Wait!

173
00:23:34,529 --> 00:23:37,529
Mama, wait! Mama!

174
00:24:22,528 --> 00:24:25,427
Do you ever come through
the door like everyone else?

175
00:24:25,527 --> 00:24:27,527
No.

176
00:24:28,527 --> 00:24:30,427
Here we go, Emmet.

177
00:24:30,527 --> 00:24:33,427
Good boy.

178
00:24:33,527 --> 00:24:36,427
Emmet, hi.

179
00:24:36,527 --> 00:24:38,527
Hey, guys.

180
00:24:40,278 --> 00:24:41,428
How are you?

181
00:24:41,528 --> 00:24:43,527
Will you marry me?

182
00:24:44,527 --> 00:24:47,427
That's the first time
this month he's asked.

183
00:24:47,527 --> 00:24:48,428
He'll get tired of it.

184
00:24:48,528 --> 00:24:50,427
Routine is good.

185
00:24:50,527 --> 00:24:51,677
My mother says so.

186
00:24:56,526 --> 00:24:57,676
So?

187
00:25:02,526 --> 00:25:04,526
She's gone.

188
00:25:11,526 --> 00:25:14,426
He looks like you, Cooper.

189
00:25:14,526 --> 00:25:17,426
Oh, yeah.

190
00:25:17,526 --> 00:25:19,426
That's what everybody says.

191
00:25:19,526 --> 00:25:24,426
We all look alike,
the whole family down through the ages.

192
00:25:24,526 --> 00:25:27,425
Toss our pictures in the air.

193
00:25:27,525 --> 00:25:29,425
When they came down,
they'd all look like me.

194
00:25:29,525 --> 00:25:32,425
Well, I don't look like anyone.

195
00:25:32,525 --> 00:25:34,525
Is that you, Cat?

196
00:25:36,525 --> 00:25:38,425
No.

197
00:25:38,525 --> 00:25:41,425
That's mama,
mama a long time ago.

198
00:25:41,525 --> 00:25:43,425
Oh, it's just that...

199
00:25:43,525 --> 00:25:45,425
We look so much
the same, I know.

200
00:25:45,525 --> 00:25:47,425
Yeah.

201
00:25:47,525 --> 00:25:50,425
There. That's
who I look like.

202
00:25:50,525 --> 00:25:53,425
Look. See?

203
00:25:53,525 --> 00:25:54,426
Yeah, I do.

204
00:25:54,526 --> 00:25:56,424
I do.

205
00:25:56,524 --> 00:25:57,674
Sounds like a wedding.

206
00:25:59,524 --> 00:26:01,524
But you look like mama, too.

207
00:26:05,524 --> 00:26:09,424
Well, well, look
who's come for a visit.

208
00:26:09,524 --> 00:26:10,424
Hello, Cooper.

209
00:26:10,524 --> 00:26:11,425
Hey.

210
00:26:11,525 --> 00:26:13,424
Would you hold that, Journey?

211
00:26:13,524 --> 00:26:16,424
Oh, Emmet. Well,
nice to see you again.

212
00:26:16,524 --> 00:26:18,424
How's my boy?

213
00:26:18,524 --> 00:26:19,425
Ha ha ha!

214
00:26:19,525 --> 00:26:21,424
Yeah. Come on.

215
00:26:21,524 --> 00:26:23,424
Yeah.

216
00:26:23,524 --> 00:26:25,423
How are you?

217
00:26:25,523 --> 00:26:26,424
Sorry.

218
00:26:26,524 --> 00:26:28,423
I didn't mean to do that.

219
00:26:28,523 --> 00:26:30,423
No, no.
That's all right.

220
00:26:30,523 --> 00:26:32,523
You can take as many
pictures as you want.

221
00:26:36,523 --> 00:26:39,423
Trot, trot to Boston,

222
00:26:39,523 --> 00:26:41,423
trot, trot to Lynn,

223
00:26:41,523 --> 00:26:42,424
watch out, little boy,

224
00:26:42,524 --> 00:26:45,423
or you'll fall in.

225
00:26:45,523 --> 00:26:47,423
Trot, trot to Boston,

226
00:26:47,523 --> 00:26:49,423
trot, trot to Lynn,

227
00:26:49,523 --> 00:26:51,423
watch out, little boy,

228
00:26:51,523 --> 00:26:53,423
or you'll fall in.

229
00:26:53,523 --> 00:26:56,422
Trot, trot to Boston,

230
00:26:56,522 --> 00:26:57,423
trot, trot to Lynn,

231
00:26:57,523 --> 00:26:59,422
watch out, little boy,

232
00:26:59,522 --> 00:27:02,422
or you'll fall in.

233
00:27:02,522 --> 00:27:04,957
Teenaged Journey, narrating:
<i>We're in the garden, up and down I go,</i>

234
00:27:05,057 --> 00:27:08,422
<i>my eyes fastened on white
buttons against a blue shirt.</i>

235
00:27:08,522 --> 00:27:10,422
<i>The smell of summer
fills the air,</i>

236
00:27:10,522 --> 00:27:12,422
<i>and voices rising and falling</i>

237
00:27:12,522 --> 00:27:14,422
<i>and laughter.</i>

238
00:27:14,522 --> 00:27:15,423
<i>Watch out, little boy.</i>

239
00:27:15,523 --> 00:27:17,422
<i>Or you'll...</i>

240
00:27:17,522 --> 00:27:21,422
<i>I look at the shirt button
and then the neck,</i>

241
00:27:21,522 --> 00:27:23,422
<i>but there's no face.</i>

242
00:27:23,522 --> 00:27:27,521
<i>It's my father, I know,
but there's no face.</i>

243
00:27:29,521 --> 00:27:33,421
Ha ha ha!

244
00:27:33,521 --> 00:27:35,421
Ha ha ha!

245
00:27:35,521 --> 00:27:36,422
Oh, yeah.

246
00:27:36,522 --> 00:27:38,421
Ha ha ha.

247
00:27:38,521 --> 00:27:40,421
Yeah. There you go,
big fella.

248
00:27:40,521 --> 00:27:42,521
Ah.

249
00:27:46,521 --> 00:27:49,421
Things don't look the
same through the camera,

250
00:27:49,521 --> 00:27:52,421
not the way they
are in real life.

251
00:27:52,521 --> 00:27:56,420
Sometimes, and sometimes
pictures show us

252
00:27:56,520 --> 00:27:57,421
what is really there.

253
00:27:57,521 --> 00:27:59,420
How can that be?

254
00:27:59,520 --> 00:28:00,421
I don't know, Journey.

255
00:28:00,521 --> 00:28:03,420
Maybe that's why
people take pictures...

256
00:28:03,520 --> 00:28:05,420
To see what's there.

257
00:28:05,520 --> 00:28:09,520
What do you mean,
"to see what is there"?

258
00:28:11,520 --> 00:28:12,670
Look.

259
00:28:22,520 --> 00:28:25,419
What does he mean?

260
00:28:25,519 --> 00:28:28,419
That could be you, Journey.

261
00:28:28,519 --> 00:28:30,419
Is that daddy?
It's him, isn't it?

262
00:28:30,519 --> 00:28:31,420
Two of a kind.

263
00:28:31,520 --> 00:28:33,419
It's grandfather, Journey.

264
00:28:33,519 --> 00:28:35,419
Grandfather.

265
00:28:35,519 --> 00:28:38,419
And you look like him.

266
00:28:38,519 --> 00:28:40,419
You are like him.

267
00:28:40,519 --> 00:28:42,519
No.

268
00:28:45,519 --> 00:28:47,419
Cat, I need some milk.

269
00:28:47,519 --> 00:28:48,420
Coming!

270
00:28:48,520 --> 00:28:50,419
I'll come with you.

271
00:28:50,519 --> 00:28:51,420
Come on, Emmet.

272
00:28:51,520 --> 00:28:53,519
Let's go see
Journey's grandmother.

273
00:29:01,518 --> 00:29:03,518
No.

274
00:29:06,518 --> 00:29:08,418
You've got to try.

275
00:29:08,518 --> 00:29:10,418
I can't.

276
00:29:10,518 --> 00:29:11,418
You've got to.

277
00:29:11,518 --> 00:29:12,419
Stop arguing.

278
00:29:12,519 --> 00:29:14,418
We're not arguing.
We're having a dialogue.

279
00:29:14,518 --> 00:29:16,418
It sounds like arguing.

280
00:29:16,518 --> 00:29:18,418
I don't know
how to drive to town.

281
00:29:18,518 --> 00:29:19,418
You'll learn.

282
00:29:19,518 --> 00:29:20,418
I don't want to learn.

283
00:29:20,518 --> 00:29:21,418
You'll be glad someday

284
00:29:21,518 --> 00:29:22,419
to know how to drive!

285
00:29:22,519 --> 00:29:24,417
Why?

286
00:29:24,517 --> 00:29:25,418
I'm an old man.

287
00:29:25,518 --> 00:29:27,417
If I die behind the wheel,

288
00:29:27,517 --> 00:29:29,417
you'll be able to drive.

289
00:29:29,517 --> 00:29:31,417
I'm only a boy.

290
00:29:31,517 --> 00:29:32,418
So drive like a boy.

291
00:29:32,518 --> 00:29:34,417
Just a minute.
Come on over here.

292
00:29:34,517 --> 00:29:36,417
Stand there.

293
00:29:36,517 --> 00:29:37,418
Not another family picture.

294
00:29:37,518 --> 00:29:39,417
Yes. Lottie!

295
00:29:39,517 --> 00:29:41,417
Lottie!

296
00:29:41,517 --> 00:29:43,517
A picture, Lottie.
Get a hat.

297
00:29:46,517 --> 00:29:49,417
It's hot. Why
are we doing this?

298
00:29:49,517 --> 00:29:50,418
I'm not an actor, Marcus.

299
00:29:50,518 --> 00:29:52,417
I'm a hot, old woman.

300
00:29:52,517 --> 00:29:54,516
You're a fetching
hot, old woman.

301
00:29:56,516 --> 00:29:58,416
Timer's set.

302
00:29:58,516 --> 00:30:01,416
10, 9, 8...

303
00:30:01,516 --> 00:30:02,416
7...
Why?

304
00:30:02,516 --> 00:30:03,416
6...

305
00:30:03,516 --> 00:30:04,417
5...

306
00:30:04,517 --> 00:30:06,416
4...

307
00:30:06,516 --> 00:30:07,416
3...

308
00:30:07,516 --> 00:30:08,417
Don't look up.

309
00:30:08,517 --> 00:30:10,516
2, 1.

310
00:30:17,267 --> 00:30:18,417
Oh, no.

311
00:30:18,517 --> 00:30:20,416
Never mind.

312
00:30:20,516 --> 00:30:22,516
Let's get going.

313
00:30:24,515 --> 00:30:27,415
I've got rolls
of film to drop off,

314
00:30:27,515 --> 00:30:29,415
pictures to pick up.

315
00:30:29,515 --> 00:30:33,415
And, uh, other things
to get in town.

316
00:30:33,515 --> 00:30:34,416
Other things?
What other things?

317
00:30:34,516 --> 00:30:38,415
Things. Photo things.

318
00:30:38,515 --> 00:30:39,416
Come on, Journey.

319
00:30:39,516 --> 00:30:43,415
I'll drive
when we get into town.

320
00:30:43,515 --> 00:30:45,515
You drive now.

321
00:30:48,515 --> 00:30:50,415
I can't reach the pedals.

322
00:30:50,515 --> 00:30:52,415
I can't even see out.

323
00:30:52,515 --> 00:30:54,414
Here. Sit on this pillow.

324
00:30:54,514 --> 00:30:56,514
Wait. This is
the brake.

325
00:30:58,265 --> 00:30:59,415
No. The clutch.
The clutch!

326
00:30:59,515 --> 00:31:02,414
You said...
I know. I know.

327
00:31:02,514 --> 00:31:04,514
Ha ha ha.

328
00:31:07,514 --> 00:31:10,414
I remember when he
taught Min how to drive.

329
00:31:10,514 --> 00:31:12,414
Oh, that was some yelling.

330
00:31:12,514 --> 00:31:14,414
Lots of yelling.

331
00:31:14,514 --> 00:31:15,415
Min never did take to anyone

332
00:31:15,515 --> 00:31:18,414
telling her what to do,
especially Marcus.

333
00:31:18,514 --> 00:31:20,514
Especially Marcus.

334
00:31:22,264 --> 00:31:23,414
It's funny how some people

335
00:31:23,514 --> 00:31:25,413
bump up against each other.

336
00:31:25,513 --> 00:31:29,413
Yeah, but they did all the time,

337
00:31:29,513 --> 00:31:32,413
even when Min was little.

338
00:31:32,513 --> 00:31:35,413
Marcus has his way.

339
00:31:35,513 --> 00:31:38,413
She never liked his way.

340
00:31:38,513 --> 00:31:39,414
Well, he never liked
her way, either, Lottie.

341
00:31:39,514 --> 00:31:42,513
Ha ha! That's true.

342
00:31:48,513 --> 00:31:50,513
Maybe she'll come back.

343
00:31:52,513 --> 00:31:54,512
Maybe not.

344
00:32:01,512 --> 00:32:04,512
Maybe it's better
if she stays away.

345
00:32:16,512 --> 00:32:17,662
Hello?

346
00:32:22,512 --> 00:32:23,662
Hello?

347
00:32:29,511 --> 00:32:30,661
Min?

348
00:32:40,511 --> 00:32:42,511
Here.

349
00:32:44,511 --> 00:32:46,411
You sure you wanna stay?

350
00:32:46,511 --> 00:32:48,411
You're a good worker.

351
00:32:48,511 --> 00:32:50,511
Gotta move on.

352
00:32:52,510 --> 00:32:54,410
Maybe you'll come
through here again.

353
00:32:54,510 --> 00:32:57,510
Thank you.

354
00:33:47,509 --> 00:33:49,409
That's it.
He's doing all right.

355
00:33:49,509 --> 00:33:50,410
I can't do this.

356
00:33:50,510 --> 00:33:52,408
Why do you have a car like this?

357
00:33:52,508 --> 00:33:54,408
I love this car.

358
00:33:54,508 --> 00:33:55,409
There aren't many left.

359
00:33:55,509 --> 00:33:57,408
They're extinct, like
the passenger pigeon.

360
00:33:57,508 --> 00:33:58,409
That's what grandma says.

361
00:33:58,509 --> 00:34:00,408
Oh, does she?

362
00:34:00,508 --> 00:34:02,408
Well. Ha ha!

363
00:34:02,508 --> 00:34:03,409
Hold it steady now.

364
00:34:03,509 --> 00:34:05,408
Come on.
Hold it steady.

365
00:34:05,508 --> 00:34:08,408
If we crash,
he'll photograph it as it happens.

366
00:34:08,508 --> 00:34:11,408
Hold it there now.
That's right.

367
00:34:11,508 --> 00:34:13,408
Good.

368
00:34:13,508 --> 00:34:14,408
Hey!

369
00:34:14,508 --> 00:34:15,409
Millie!

370
00:34:15,509 --> 00:34:17,408
Hey!

371
00:34:17,508 --> 00:34:19,408
Hey!

372
00:34:19,508 --> 00:34:20,658
Oh!

373
00:34:22,507 --> 00:34:24,507
Oh.

374
00:34:27,507 --> 00:34:29,407
Hey, jed's back!

375
00:34:29,507 --> 00:34:30,407
Hi!

376
00:34:30,507 --> 00:34:31,657
Hey, Marcus!

377
00:34:37,507 --> 00:34:39,407
Hey, grandpa, look.

378
00:34:39,507 --> 00:34:41,407
Quick! Take a picture.

379
00:34:41,507 --> 00:34:42,408
Oh. Oh!

380
00:34:42,508 --> 00:34:44,507
Cooper! Hey!

381
00:34:48,507 --> 00:34:50,407
Ahh.

382
00:34:50,507 --> 00:34:51,407
You know?

383
00:34:51,507 --> 00:34:52,407
Huh?

384
00:34:52,507 --> 00:34:54,406
I bet that picture of all of us

385
00:34:54,506 --> 00:34:57,406
looking at the airplane,
it'll be fine.

386
00:34:57,506 --> 00:35:00,406
I think so, too, Journey.

387
00:35:00,506 --> 00:35:01,656
Two of a kind.

388
00:35:20,506 --> 00:35:22,405
Come on!
It's coming down harder!

389
00:35:22,505 --> 00:35:24,405
Hurry up. Let's go.

390
00:35:24,505 --> 00:35:26,405
Hurry up, you guys.

391
00:35:26,505 --> 00:35:28,405
I am hurrying.

392
00:35:28,505 --> 00:35:29,406
We can't get 'em all.

393
00:35:29,506 --> 00:35:31,405
Don't we have enough?

394
00:35:31,505 --> 00:35:34,505
Come on, Cat.
Come on, Journey.

395
00:35:36,505 --> 00:35:38,405
Come on, boy.
Let's get inside.

396
00:35:38,505 --> 00:35:40,405
It's wet.

397
00:35:40,505 --> 00:35:42,405
Oh, let's get in there.

398
00:35:42,505 --> 00:35:43,406
Hurry up.

399
00:35:43,506 --> 00:35:45,505
Journey, move faster, go, quick.

400
00:35:49,256 --> 00:35:50,406
Whoa!

401
00:35:50,506 --> 00:35:53,404
Oh, let's get inside.

402
00:35:53,504 --> 00:35:55,404
Here we are.

403
00:35:55,504 --> 00:35:57,404
Saved from the rain.

404
00:35:57,504 --> 00:35:58,405
Well done.

405
00:35:58,505 --> 00:36:00,404
Oh, smell those.

406
00:36:00,504 --> 00:36:03,404
Oh, that's a wonderful smell,
isn't it?

407
00:36:03,504 --> 00:36:04,405
Oh, yeah.

408
00:36:04,505 --> 00:36:06,404
Well, there are ants everywhere.

409
00:36:06,504 --> 00:36:07,404
There are, yeah.

410
00:36:07,504 --> 00:36:08,404
Well, just regard them

411
00:36:08,504 --> 00:36:09,404
like they're sightseers

412
00:36:09,504 --> 00:36:10,405
or like they're visitors.

413
00:36:10,505 --> 00:36:12,404
Marcus...

414
00:36:12,504 --> 00:36:14,404
It's new.

415
00:36:14,504 --> 00:36:16,504
I bought it in town.

416
00:36:21,503 --> 00:36:23,503
Ha ha.

417
00:36:26,503 --> 00:36:28,403
Marcus,
I have spots in front of my eyes.

418
00:36:28,503 --> 00:36:30,403
I can't see.

419
00:36:30,503 --> 00:36:32,403
Go away and be a farmer,
will you?

420
00:36:32,503 --> 00:36:35,403
I'm a farmer who
takes pictures, Lottie.

421
00:36:35,503 --> 00:36:37,403
I'm a photographer farmer.

422
00:36:37,503 --> 00:36:39,403
Ha ha ha.

423
00:36:39,503 --> 00:36:40,404
Marcus, you've got to learn

424
00:36:40,504 --> 00:36:43,503
you cannot always have
things your own way.

425
00:37:24,501 --> 00:37:26,501
Maybe the chickens.

426
00:38:59,498 --> 00:39:01,398
You moved the camera.

427
00:39:01,498 --> 00:39:03,398
That's why the edges are fuzzy.

428
00:39:03,498 --> 00:39:05,398
It's not a good picture,
I guess.

429
00:39:05,498 --> 00:39:08,398
Journey, it's
a wonderful picture.

430
00:39:08,498 --> 00:39:10,398
But I moved the camera.

431
00:39:10,498 --> 00:39:13,398
You did, but you
see how Emmet and I

432
00:39:13,498 --> 00:39:15,398
look like we're
the only ones there,

433
00:39:15,498 --> 00:39:19,398
how we look like we're
wrapped in a cocoon,

434
00:39:19,498 --> 00:39:21,397
away from the rest of the world?

435
00:39:21,497 --> 00:39:23,397
See how the edge is framed?

436
00:39:23,497 --> 00:39:27,397
Yeah, but it's not perfect.

437
00:39:27,497 --> 00:39:28,398
Perfect?

438
00:39:28,498 --> 00:39:30,397
What's perfect?

439
00:39:30,497 --> 00:39:32,397
Journey...

440
00:39:32,497 --> 00:39:35,397
Things don't have to be
perfect to make them fine.

441
00:39:35,497 --> 00:39:37,397
Now, that goes for pictures,

442
00:39:37,497 --> 00:39:39,397
and that goes for life.

443
00:39:39,497 --> 00:39:42,497
Things could be good enough.

444
00:39:45,497 --> 00:39:47,397
Grandfather...

445
00:39:47,497 --> 00:39:48,398
Hmm?

446
00:39:48,498 --> 00:39:50,396
Do you think mama left

447
00:39:50,496 --> 00:39:53,396
because I wasn't good enough?

448
00:39:53,496 --> 00:39:55,396
No.

449
00:39:55,496 --> 00:39:58,396
No, Journey.

450
00:39:58,496 --> 00:40:00,396
You know that
I tell you the truth,

451
00:40:00,496 --> 00:40:03,396
even when you
don't like to hear it.

452
00:40:03,496 --> 00:40:06,396
Sometimes you tell me the truth.

453
00:40:06,496 --> 00:40:08,396
You say that mama
won't come back,

454
00:40:08,496 --> 00:40:10,396
and I know she will.

455
00:40:10,496 --> 00:40:11,397
That wasn't the truth.

456
00:40:11,497 --> 00:40:15,396
You need someone to blame,
Journey, is that it?

457
00:40:15,496 --> 00:40:17,396
Well, here's an important truth.

458
00:40:17,496 --> 00:40:20,395
It is not your fault.

459
00:40:20,495 --> 00:40:21,396
It's not all mama's fault.

460
00:40:21,496 --> 00:40:25,395
No. I can see that
you can't blame Min,

461
00:40:25,495 --> 00:40:26,396
and that's all right.

462
00:40:26,496 --> 00:40:28,395
I remember things.

463
00:40:28,495 --> 00:40:30,395
I remember
"trot, trot to Boston."

464
00:40:30,495 --> 00:40:32,395
I do.

465
00:40:32,495 --> 00:40:35,395
Oh, I'm not surprised
that you remember.

466
00:40:35,495 --> 00:40:37,395
You were very little,

467
00:40:37,495 --> 00:40:41,395
but you wanted to hear
that rhyme over and over.

468
00:40:41,495 --> 00:40:42,396
I remember I sat on daddy's
lap before he went away.

469
00:40:42,496 --> 00:40:44,395
I remember his buttons,

470
00:40:44,495 --> 00:40:48,395
that he held my hands
and wouldn't let me fall.

471
00:40:48,495 --> 00:40:50,394
Mama and papa kept me safe

472
00:40:50,494 --> 00:40:52,394
and cared for me until you...

473
00:40:52,494 --> 00:40:54,394
Until I made them go away?

474
00:40:54,494 --> 00:40:57,494
You think I did that?

475
00:40:59,494 --> 00:41:02,394
Where are the pictures?
I want to see them.

476
00:41:02,494 --> 00:41:03,395
What pictures?

477
00:41:03,495 --> 00:41:06,394
Of papa, mama, me, and Cat

478
00:41:06,494 --> 00:41:08,394
when we were babies, like Emmet,

479
00:41:08,494 --> 00:41:10,394
when I was on papa's knees
and he sang to me.

480
00:41:10,494 --> 00:41:11,395
There weren't many.

481
00:41:11,495 --> 00:41:13,394
I don't need many.

482
00:41:13,494 --> 00:41:15,394
They're gone.

483
00:41:15,494 --> 00:41:17,394
Gone? You mean
mama took them?

484
00:41:17,494 --> 00:41:19,394
The truth?

485
00:41:19,494 --> 00:41:20,394
Yes.

486
00:41:20,494 --> 00:41:22,393
Did she take them?

487
00:41:22,493 --> 00:41:23,394
No, Journey.

488
00:41:23,494 --> 00:41:25,493
Your mama tore them up.

489
00:41:59,492 --> 00:42:00,642
Marcus?

490
00:42:03,243 --> 00:42:04,393
He blames me.

491
00:42:04,493 --> 00:42:07,392
Oh, he blames you.
You blame her.

492
00:42:07,492 --> 00:42:09,392
All this blame.

493
00:42:09,492 --> 00:42:11,392
How could she
leave the children?

494
00:42:11,492 --> 00:42:14,492
How could she do that?

495
00:42:18,492 --> 00:42:21,491
I don't know.

496
00:42:33,491 --> 00:42:36,391
Do you remember when
min used to sit on my lap...

497
00:42:36,491 --> 00:42:39,391
When she was little?

498
00:42:39,491 --> 00:42:41,391
She'd stay for a while,

499
00:42:41,491 --> 00:42:45,391
and then she wandered.

500
00:42:45,491 --> 00:42:49,390
Remember we'd find her
way down the road,

501
00:42:49,490 --> 00:42:51,390
way out in the Meadow,

502
00:42:51,490 --> 00:42:54,390
as if she was going away?

503
00:42:54,490 --> 00:42:57,490
As if she was going away then.

504
00:42:59,490 --> 00:43:01,390
Oh, I don't know, Marcus.

505
00:43:01,490 --> 00:43:03,490
I... I don't know.

506
00:43:12,490 --> 00:43:16,390
I loved her when she was little.

507
00:43:16,490 --> 00:43:18,390
Yeah.

508
00:43:18,490 --> 00:43:20,389
You're trying
not to love her now,

509
00:43:20,489 --> 00:43:22,489
just like Journey's
trying not to love you.

510
00:44:02,488 --> 00:44:04,388
I don't believe
you're sick, Journey.

511
00:44:04,488 --> 00:44:05,389
If you are,

512
00:44:05,489 --> 00:44:08,388
you like us to bring you
ginger ale and soup.

513
00:44:08,488 --> 00:44:09,389
I have a sore throat.

514
00:44:09,489 --> 00:44:11,388
Yeah, let's see.

515
00:44:11,488 --> 00:44:13,388
I have a temperature, too.

516
00:44:13,488 --> 00:44:14,389
How many quilts
do you have here?

517
00:44:14,489 --> 00:44:18,388
1, 2, 3... a quilt, bedspread.

518
00:44:18,488 --> 00:44:19,388
You've got five blankets.
It's summer.

519
00:44:19,488 --> 00:44:21,387
You may turn into a butterfly.

520
00:44:21,487 --> 00:44:23,387
Cat...

521
00:44:23,487 --> 00:44:27,487
Mama tore up our pictures.

522
00:44:30,487 --> 00:44:31,637
I know.

523
00:44:34,237 --> 00:44:35,387
Cat!

524
00:44:35,487 --> 00:44:36,388
You're not sick, Journey!

525
00:44:36,488 --> 00:44:38,387
You're hiding out.

526
00:44:38,487 --> 00:44:41,487
You always hide out
when things go wrong.

527
00:44:47,487 --> 00:44:48,637
Here! Listen
to the music.

528
00:45:29,485 --> 00:45:31,385
Hi.

529
00:45:31,485 --> 00:45:32,635
Hi.

530
00:45:34,485 --> 00:45:36,385
You feeling better?

531
00:45:36,485 --> 00:45:37,386
Cat made me get up.

532
00:45:37,486 --> 00:45:41,485
Cat's a woman of action.

533
00:45:42,485 --> 00:45:45,385
She don't believe much
in introspection.

534
00:45:45,485 --> 00:45:48,384
Introspection?

535
00:45:48,484 --> 00:45:49,385
That's what you've been doing

536
00:45:49,485 --> 00:45:51,384
for the past two days,

537
00:45:51,484 --> 00:45:52,385
thinking mostly about yourself.

538
00:45:52,485 --> 00:45:55,384
You see, Cat...

539
00:45:55,484 --> 00:45:58,384
She believes
that if she keeps busy,

540
00:45:58,484 --> 00:46:01,384
all of her problems
will just go away.

541
00:46:01,484 --> 00:46:03,384
Does that work?

542
00:46:03,484 --> 00:46:06,484
No more than thinking works.

543
00:46:08,484 --> 00:46:11,384
But if you notice,
my garden is... what?

544
00:46:11,484 --> 00:46:13,384
Twice the size it was last year.

545
00:46:13,484 --> 00:46:16,384
We all do the best we can.

546
00:46:16,484 --> 00:46:18,383
Your sister and I,

547
00:46:18,483 --> 00:46:22,483
we garden ourselves
into a kind of madness.

548
00:46:23,483 --> 00:46:27,483
You think yourself
into a sore throat.

549
00:46:29,483 --> 00:46:31,483
And your grandpa takes pictures.

550
00:46:37,483 --> 00:46:40,483
Ha ha ha!

551
00:46:46,483 --> 00:46:49,382
He's going to take
a picture of us now,

552
00:46:49,482 --> 00:46:50,383
that old buzzard.

553
00:46:50,483 --> 00:46:53,382
How do you know?
He didn't look here.

554
00:46:53,482 --> 00:46:54,383
Oh, yes, he did.

555
00:46:54,483 --> 00:46:57,482
I saw his eyes roll to the side.

556
00:46:59,233 --> 00:47:00,383
Why are we whispering?

557
00:47:00,483 --> 00:47:02,382
I don't know,

558
00:47:02,482 --> 00:47:05,382
but I know I'm the smartest
woman on this porch.

559
00:47:05,482 --> 00:47:08,382
When he takes the picture,
we'll cover our face.

560
00:47:08,482 --> 00:47:10,382
1, 2, 3...

