Sometimes there's truth,
duncan's right,

842
01:14:43,426 --> 01:14:46,326
but do you see that
picture of me there?

843
01:14:46,426 --> 01:14:47,327
Don't we look like
the perfect family?

844
01:14:47,427 --> 01:14:49,326
My brother Fergus
there on the left

845
01:14:49,426 --> 01:14:51,326
was pinching the devil out of me

846
01:14:51,426 --> 01:14:52,327
when that picture was taken.

847
01:14:52,427 --> 01:14:54,326
He did that all my life.

848
01:14:54,426 --> 01:14:57,326
He still does.

849
01:14:57,426 --> 01:14:59,426
Sometimes the truth is
somewhere behind the pictures,

850
01:14:59,526 --> 01:15:00,676
not in them.

851
01:15:02,426 --> 01:15:06,326
Well, I'd better
go hose him off.

852
01:15:06,426 --> 01:15:08,325
It's early, Journey.

853
01:15:08,425 --> 01:15:09,326
Do Marcus and Lottie
know where you are?

854
01:15:09,426 --> 01:15:11,325
You want a ride?

855
01:15:11,425 --> 01:15:14,325
I'm going to ride him home
on my bike, Mr. Macdougal

856
01:15:14,425 --> 01:15:15,575
all right, then.
I'm off.

857
01:15:18,425 --> 01:15:20,325
Bye.

858
01:15:20,425 --> 01:15:21,325
Bye.

859
01:15:21,425 --> 01:15:22,575
Bye.

860
01:15:31,425 --> 01:15:33,425
Wheezer, come on!

861
01:15:34,425 --> 01:15:36,325
Come on, come on.

862
01:15:36,425 --> 01:15:39,324
Ok, wheezer, go home.

863
01:15:39,424 --> 01:15:41,324
Go! Go! Go! Go! Go!

864
01:15:41,424 --> 01:15:42,325
Get out of here, wheezer.

865
01:15:42,425 --> 01:15:44,324
Whoo-hoo!

866
01:15:44,424 --> 01:15:45,574
Whoo-hoo!

867
01:16:26,423 --> 01:16:28,323
Yes.

868
01:16:28,423 --> 01:16:32,423
You are a wonderful mother.

869
01:16:35,174 --> 01:16:36,324
Who taught her?

870
01:16:36,424 --> 01:16:39,322
Taught her what?
How to have kittens?

871
01:16:39,422 --> 01:16:41,322
No, how to be a mother.

872
01:16:41,422 --> 01:16:42,323
Mothers know.

873
01:16:42,423 --> 01:16:44,422
Well, not all of them.

874
01:16:48,422 --> 01:16:50,322
Grandfather.

875
01:16:50,422 --> 01:16:51,323
Hmm?

876
01:16:51,423 --> 01:16:53,322
I want to take a
picture with the timer.

877
01:16:53,422 --> 01:16:55,422
Oh, no.

878
01:16:57,172 --> 01:16:58,322
In the hall, Journey.

879
01:16:58,422 --> 01:16:59,323
Oh, no.

880
01:16:59,423 --> 01:17:01,422
Now we have two of them.

881
01:17:03,422 --> 01:17:05,322
Everybody get closer.

882
01:17:05,422 --> 01:17:08,421
All right.
Get around there.

883
01:17:09,421 --> 01:17:11,321
You sound like you-know-who.

884
01:17:11,421 --> 01:17:12,321
Who?

885
01:17:12,421 --> 01:17:13,571
The photographer twins.

886
01:17:15,421 --> 01:17:17,321
There.

887
01:17:17,421 --> 01:17:18,322
We're starting.

888
01:17:18,422 --> 01:17:20,321
10...

889
01:17:20,421 --> 01:17:21,571
9...

890
01:17:29,421 --> 01:17:31,421
Quick! Camera.

891
01:17:43,171 --> 01:17:44,321
We could keep them in my room.

892
01:17:44,421 --> 01:17:47,320
Oh, I don't know.
Maybe we could.

893
01:17:47,420 --> 01:17:48,321
It's good to eat with people

894
01:17:48,421 --> 01:17:51,320
who don't have food on
their faces. But I love Emmet.

895
01:17:51,420 --> 01:17:53,320
You certainly do.

896
01:17:53,420 --> 01:17:55,420
You're a good brother,
Cooper. Thank you.

897
01:17:58,171 --> 01:17:59,321
Where's she going?

898
01:17:59,421 --> 01:18:02,320
She's going out.
Don't worry.

899
01:18:02,420 --> 01:18:04,320
She'll be back.

900
01:18:04,420 --> 01:18:05,320
She'll come back, Journey.

901
01:18:05,420 --> 01:18:06,570
She'll be back.

902
01:18:10,419 --> 01:18:13,419
Well, thanks.
I'd better get going.

903
01:18:21,419 --> 01:18:23,319
Bye. Thanks again.

904
01:18:23,419 --> 01:18:24,319
Bye, Cooper.

905
01:18:24,419 --> 01:18:25,569
Bye.

906
01:18:31,419 --> 01:18:33,419
Maybe someday I will marry him.

907
01:18:35,419 --> 01:18:38,318
Hey, come and do some gardening with me,
yeah?

908
01:18:38,418 --> 01:18:40,418
I think I'll take a
walk to the henhouse.

909
01:18:42,418 --> 01:18:44,418
Oh, I'll get it, grandfather.

910
01:18:48,418 --> 01:18:50,318
Hello.

911
01:18:50,418 --> 01:18:51,568
Journey?

912
01:18:52,418 --> 01:18:54,418
Journey, is that you?

913
01:18:57,418 --> 01:18:59,418
Journey, it's mama.

914
01:19:02,418 --> 01:19:04,418
Journey?

915
01:19:05,418 --> 01:19:07,417
Yes.

916
01:19:09,417 --> 01:19:10,567
How... how are you?

917
01:19:13,417 --> 01:19:17,317
Mama, a Cat has come...

918
01:19:17,417 --> 01:19:19,417
And the Cat's
a very good mother.

919
01:19:21,417 --> 01:19:24,317
She's staying with me...

920
01:19:24,417 --> 01:19:25,567
Forever.

921
01:20:04,167 --> 01:20:05,317
That's a new one.

922
01:20:05,417 --> 01:20:08,315
Some chicken pecked me.

923
01:20:08,415 --> 01:20:10,415
This taking pictures
is dangerous business.

924
01:20:14,166 --> 01:20:15,316
Mama called.

925
01:20:15,416 --> 01:20:18,315
She asked me how I was.

926
01:20:18,415 --> 01:20:22,415
She never said
she was sorry for leaving.

927
01:20:23,415 --> 01:20:25,315
No...

928
01:20:25,415 --> 01:20:28,415
Min doesn't want to feel guilty.

929
01:20:35,415 --> 01:20:37,314
Then mama said...

930
01:20:37,414 --> 01:20:40,414
"They were only pictures,
Journey."

931
01:20:46,414 --> 01:20:48,314
Your mama...

932
01:20:48,414 --> 01:20:52,414
Doesn't really understand
about the pictures.

933
01:20:56,414 --> 01:20:59,314
Mama wants me to visit her.

934
01:20:59,414 --> 01:21:01,314
I told her I couldn't.

935
01:21:01,414 --> 01:21:05,314
I told her I had a Cat
and kittens to take care of.

936
01:21:05,414 --> 01:21:09,313
I told her someday, maybe,

937
01:21:09,413 --> 01:21:12,313
if she sent me words
instead of money,

938
01:21:12,413 --> 01:21:13,563
I might visit her...

939
01:21:15,413 --> 01:21:16,563
Maybe.

940
01:21:19,164 --> 01:21:20,314
Grandfather?

941
01:21:20,414 --> 01:21:22,313
What, Journey?

942
01:21:22,413 --> 01:21:25,413
I told her nothing is perfect.

943
01:21:27,413 --> 01:21:29,413
Sometimes,
things are good enough.

944
01:21:35,162 --> 01:21:36,312
I like that picture.

945
01:21:36,412 --> 01:21:37,313
Hmm?

946
01:21:37,413 --> 01:21:40,312
Oh, so do I.

947
01:21:40,412 --> 01:21:42,312
Hey, is that the chicken
that pecked you?

948
01:21:42,412 --> 01:21:45,312
Ha.

949
01:21:45,412 --> 01:21:47,412
Maybe. Ha.

950
01:22:22,411 --> 01:22:23,561
Well...

951
01:22:25,411 --> 01:22:28,311
He needs things to look back on.

952
01:22:28,411 --> 01:22:31,311
Shame about the old pictures.

953
01:22:31,411 --> 01:22:33,411
Guess there's no way
to get them back.

954
01:23:15,409 --> 01:23:17,409
Where has he been?

955
01:23:20,160 --> 01:23:21,310
Do you know, Journey?

956
01:23:21,410 --> 01:23:23,309
No.

957
01:23:23,409 --> 01:23:26,409
This is his third trip
to town this week.

958
01:23:29,409 --> 01:23:33,309
Do not follow me.

959
01:23:33,409 --> 01:23:35,309
Ha ha. What's he doing?

960
01:23:35,409 --> 01:23:37,408
Well, let's find out.

961
01:23:54,408 --> 01:23:57,308
Marcus...
My darling man,

962
01:23:57,408 --> 01:23:59,308
what are you doing?

963
01:23:59,408 --> 01:24:01,408
Don't sweet-talk me, Lottie!

964
01:24:08,407 --> 01:24:11,307
Well, we could spy on him.

965
01:24:11,407 --> 01:24:14,307
Better sooner than ask him.

966
01:24:14,407 --> 01:24:16,307
I think it's more fun to keep him waiting,
don't you?

967
01:24:16,407 --> 01:24:17,557
Shh.
Yeah.

968
01:24:24,407 --> 01:24:27,407
It's locked.
Knock.

969
01:24:28,158 --> 01:24:29,308
Grandfather?

970
01:24:29,408 --> 01:24:32,407
I'm busy, busy in my office.

971
01:24:35,406 --> 01:24:38,406
Well, leave him.
Come on. Come on.

972
01:25:18,405 --> 01:25:20,305
Every third or every fourth?

973
01:25:20,405 --> 01:25:21,305
Every other.

974
01:25:21,405 --> 01:25:22,555
Third.

975
01:25:25,405 --> 01:25:28,305
Remember when we used
to make tents in the backyard?

976
01:25:28,405 --> 01:25:31,305
You liked to build the tents,

977
01:25:31,405 --> 01:25:33,305
and when you were done,

978
01:25:33,405 --> 01:25:35,304
you'd sit inside all jittery,

979
01:25:35,404 --> 01:25:38,404
waiting for something more
to happen.

980
01:25:45,404 --> 01:25:47,404
What?

981
01:25:48,404 --> 01:25:50,304
Something grandfather said...

982
01:25:50,404 --> 01:25:53,304
Mama waiting
for things to happen.

983
01:25:53,404 --> 01:25:57,304
Remember when mama
got in the tent with us once?

984
01:25:57,404 --> 01:25:59,404
Yeah.

985
01:26:01,404 --> 01:26:03,304
She sat for a minute,

986
01:26:03,404 --> 01:26:07,303
and then she looked at us
and said, "well, what now?"

987
01:26:07,403 --> 01:26:10,403
You and I, we weren't enough.

988
01:26:14,403 --> 01:26:16,303
Cat...

989
01:26:16,403 --> 01:26:20,303
Sorry I couldn't put the
pictures back together.

990
01:26:20,403 --> 01:26:22,303
I tried to make
everything all right again.

991
01:26:22,403 --> 01:26:24,303
I know.

992
01:26:24,403 --> 01:26:27,303
You and grandfather...
two of a kind.

993
01:26:27,403 --> 01:26:29,303
What do you mean?

994
01:26:29,403 --> 01:26:32,303
Why do you think grandfather
takes family pictures?

995
01:26:32,403 --> 01:26:36,302
Because he likes to,
he likes the camera.

996
01:26:36,402 --> 01:26:39,302
Don't you know that grandfather
wants to give you back

997
01:26:39,402 --> 01:26:44,402
everything that mama
took away... Family.

998
01:26:47,402 --> 01:26:49,402
Cat...

999
01:26:50,402 --> 01:26:52,402
Do you... do you hate mama?

1000
01:26:55,402 --> 01:26:57,402
I hate what she did.

1001
01:26:58,402 --> 01:27:01,402
You say that,
but do you really feel that way?

1002
01:27:03,402 --> 01:27:04,552
I'm trying.

1003
01:27:10,401 --> 01:27:13,301
Do you think she cares about us?

1004
01:27:13,401 --> 01:27:16,401
In her way, I guess.

1005
01:27:28,152 --> 01:27:29,302
What? What's wrong?

1006
01:27:29,402 --> 01:27:32,301
Wish I had grandpa's
camera right now.

1007
01:27:32,401 --> 01:27:33,302
You're red.

1008
01:27:33,402 --> 01:27:35,300
Journey!

1009
01:27:35,400 --> 01:27:37,300
I'm going to get you!

1010
01:27:37,400 --> 01:27:39,300
I'm going to kill you!
Come back here!

1011
01:27:39,400 --> 01:27:42,400
You're dead.

1012
01:27:44,400 --> 01:27:46,400
Stop running!
Come here!

1013
01:27:50,400 --> 01:27:53,300
You can run, but you can't hide!

1014
01:27:53,400 --> 01:27:54,550
Aah!

1015
01:27:56,400 --> 01:27:58,300
Can't catch me!

1016
01:27:58,400 --> 01:27:59,550
You got it all over me!

1017
01:28:03,400 --> 01:28:04,550
Can't run forever.

1018
01:28:06,399 --> 01:28:07,549
I'm going to get you!

1019
01:28:09,399 --> 01:28:11,399
Stop!

1020
01:28:15,399 --> 01:28:19,299
You're a noodle, Journey!
A noodle!

1021
01:28:19,399 --> 01:28:21,299
Journey, come back here!

1022
01:28:21,399 --> 01:28:23,299
Where are you going?

1023
01:28:23,399 --> 01:28:25,399
Journey, where are you going?

1024
01:28:31,399 --> 01:28:33,299
Hello, mother.

1025
01:28:33,399 --> 01:28:36,298
Hello, Min.

1026
01:28:36,398 --> 01:28:40,298
I've not come back.

1027
01:28:40,398 --> 01:28:42,398
I didn't think you had.

1028
01:28:48,398 --> 01:28:49,548
I...

1029
01:28:51,398 --> 01:28:53,398
I can't live here.
I just can't.

1030
01:28:57,398 --> 01:28:59,398
I'm sorry.

1031
01:29:09,397 --> 01:29:11,397
I'll write you.

1032
01:29:18,397 --> 01:29:20,397
And the children?

1033
01:29:27,397 --> 01:29:29,397
They seem happy.

1034
01:29:39,396 --> 01:29:40,546
Min.

1035
01:29:42,396 --> 01:29:45,396
Min, I've learned
to play your recorder.

1036
01:29:51,396 --> 01:29:54,396
Are you all right?

1037
01:29:57,396 --> 01:29:58,546
Yeah.

1038
01:30:01,396 --> 01:30:03,296
I...

1039
01:30:03,396 --> 01:30:05,395
I have to go.

1040
01:30:51,394 --> 01:30:53,294
Good night, Journey.

1041
01:30:53,394 --> 01:30:55,294
Were you in mama's bedroom?

1042
01:30:55,394 --> 01:30:57,294
Yeah.
Kitty went in there.

1043
01:30:57,394 --> 01:30:59,294
Are you going to bed?

1044
01:30:59,394 --> 01:31:01,294
No, I'm not going to bed yet.

1045
01:31:01,394 --> 01:31:03,393
No, I've got work to do.
Good night.

1046
01:33:34,388 --> 01:33:36,288
Where are your shoes?

1047
01:33:36,388 --> 01:33:39,288
What is all this?

1048
01:33:39,388 --> 01:33:41,388
Don't talk for a minute.

1049
01:33:44,388 --> 01:33:46,288
5... 4...

1050
01:33:46,388 --> 01:33:49,288
3... 2...

1051
01:33:49,388 --> 01:33:51,388
1... yeah.

1052
01:33:59,388 --> 01:34:01,288
This is an enlarger.

1053
01:34:01,388 --> 01:34:04,387
The red light is for developing.

1054
01:34:06,138 --> 01:34:07,288
A darkroom?

1055
01:34:07,388 --> 01:34:09,287
You did all this?

1056
01:34:09,387 --> 01:34:11,287
They're black and white
pictures.

1057
01:34:11,387 --> 01:34:14,387
They're pictures from the past.

1058
01:34:22,387 --> 01:34:25,387
Now, this is a fine picture.

1059
01:34:28,387 --> 01:34:30,287
Not perfect.

1060
01:34:30,387 --> 01:34:32,286
But good enough.

1061
01:34:32,386 --> 01:34:33,536
Ha ha.

1062
01:34:36,386 --> 01:34:38,386
And there's more.

1063
01:34:44,386 --> 01:34:46,386
Mama's pictures.

1064
01:34:48,386 --> 01:34:50,286
There's a baby.

1065
01:34:50,386 --> 01:34:52,386
This one.

1066
01:35:08,385 --> 01:35:10,385
That baby...

1067
01:35:14,385 --> 01:35:16,385
Is you.

1068
01:35:39,384 --> 01:35:42,384
That's not the face I remember.

1069
01:35:47,384 --> 01:35:48,534
And now...

1070
01:35:50,135 --> 01:35:51,285
The other picture.

1071
01:35:51,385 --> 01:35:53,384
I know.

1072
01:35:55,384 --> 01:35:57,384
I already know.

1073
01:36:00,384 --> 01:36:03,283
It was your lap I sat on.

1074
01:36:03,383 --> 01:36:06,283
You sang "trot, trot to Boston,"

1075
01:36:06,383 --> 01:36:09,283
not papa.

1076
01:36:09,383 --> 01:36:10,284
It was your shirt,

1077
01:36:10,384 --> 01:36:14,283
your button I remember,

1078
01:36:14,383 --> 01:36:15,533
your face.

1079
01:36:18,383 --> 01:36:20,283
It was you who took care of me,

1080
01:36:20,383 --> 01:36:22,283
not papa.

1081
01:36:22,383 --> 01:36:24,383
It was you.

1082
01:36:42,382 --> 01:36:43,532
And this is when you knew.

1083
01:37:05,381 --> 01:37:07,281
Teenaged Journey, narrating:
<i>That summer night,</i>

1084
01:37:07,381 --> 01:37:10,281
<i>grandfather and I walked
out through the barn.</i>

1085
01:37:10,381 --> 01:37:13,281
<i>I trailed my fingers
along the wood walls.</i>

1086
01:37:13,381 --> 01:37:15,281
<i>I touched the hay,</i>

1087
01:37:15,381 --> 01:37:18,381
<i>as if touching it
somehow made it mine.</i>

1088
01:37:30,381 --> 01:37:32,380
<i>Once they loved me.</i>

1089
01:37:35,380 --> 01:37:37,280
<i>Teenaged when we opened the door</i>

1090
01:37:37,380 --> 01:37:40,280
<i>and walked out of the barn,</i>

1091
01:37:40,380 --> 01:37:42,280
<i>the night had gone,</i>

1092
01:37:42,380 --> 01:37:49,380
<i>and the sun had come up.</i>

